e efficiently by doing what they are shown, and then are more easily able to comprehend the subject. We need more people with ideas to improve the way in which we teach these kids, which would save a lot more money than using social programs or relying on the government to help out. &#10;Bascially, the way I see it, if a child gets lucky, goes through his or her entire school k-12, and learns subjects at a lower than average level, as the schools have flawed systems and lower the passing grades so one would not need to work as hard to graduate, then that student will probably have only one choice in which they are interested in, and have limited knowledge of that field due to the inefficiency of the school system therefore becoming a failure, created by these schools. I would like to see more unique niche subjects being taught and have most of them be manditory, therefore having the student be able to pull out a wealth of knowedge as opposed to a narrow path that will lead to non success. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1307" language="en" documentId="4732" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="kubedawg" date="31st October 2006 03:06 AM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.volconvo.com/forums/showthread.php?t=12481&amp;page=1" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4732" notes="" title="Public Schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="591"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="592" end="1307"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>